+# Copilot Cloud Agent Instructions
+
+## Quick Start
+
+Read the codebase documentation before making changes ‚Äî it is comprehensive and accurate:
+
+- `docs/codebase/STACK.md` ‚Äî runtime, dependencies, key commands
+- `docs/codebase/STRUCTURE.md` ‚Äî file map, entry points, module boundaries
+- `docs/codebase/ARCHITECTURE.md` ‚Äî pipeline flow, module responsibilities, reused patterns
+- `docs/codebase/CONVENTIONS.md` ‚Äî naming rules, import conventions, error handling style
+- `docs/codebase/CONCERNS.md` ‚Äî known risks, tech debt, fragile areas
+- `docs/codebase/TESTING.md` ‚Äî testing status (no automated tests exist)
+- `docs/codebase/INTEGRATIONS.md` ‚Äî external systems, data stores, file I/O
+
+Also read `AGENTS.md` (project guidelines) and `BACKLOG.md` (task tracking).
+
+## What This Project Is
+
+An NBA DFS lineup optimizer for DraftKings. It generates, ranks, and exports fantasy lineups using linear programming (PuLP + HiGHS solver). It is a **single-user, locally-run desktop tool** with no web API, no database, and no network calls.
+
+## Architecture (Sequential File-Based Pipeline)
+
+```
+DKEntries.csv + NBA-Projs-*.csv
+       ‚îÇ
+       ‚ñº
+[Engine] ‚Üí lineup-pool-{timestamp}.csv
+       ‚îÇ
+       ‚ñº
+[Ranker] ‚Üí ranked-lineups-{timestamp}.csv
+       ‚îÇ
+       ‚ñº
+[Exporter] ‚Üí upload-ready-DKEntries-{timestamp}.csv
+       ‚îÇ
+       ‚ñº
+[Exposure Report] ‚Üí console output
+```
+
+**Alternate path:** `--late_swap` runs `late_swapper.py` instead of the standard pipeline.
+
+### Key modules and their responsibilities
+
+| Module | Owns | Must NOT own |
+|--------|------|-------------|
+| `src/nba_optimizer/engine.py` | LP model, parallel solving, slot optimization | Ranking, export |
+| `src/nba_optimizer/ranker.py` | Lineup scoring by weighted rank metrics | Generation, export |
+| `src/nba_optimizer/exporter.py` | DraftKings CSV template mapping | Ranking, optimization |
+| `src/nba_optimizer/exposure_report.py` | Post-export player exposure analytics | Everything else |
+| `src/nba_optimizer/late_swapper.py` | Lock detection, constrained re-optimization | Full lineup generation |
+| `src/nba_optimizer/config.py` | Config dataclass, env var loading, constants | Business logic |
+| `src/nba_optimizer/utils.py` | File discovery, ID parsing, CSV utilities | Module-specific logic |
+| `src/nba_optimizer/orchestrator.py` | Pipeline orchestration, Config injection | Core logic |
+| `scripts/run_optimizer.py` | CLI entry point (thin wrapper) | Core logic |
+
+**Do not move export, ranking, or report logic into the engine.** Keep module responsibilities separated.
+
+## Environment Setup
+
+```bash
+# Install the project in editable mode (this is the standard install path)
+pip install -e .
+```
+
+### Environment variables (configured via `.env`, loaded by python-dotenv)
+
+| Variable | Purpose |
+|----------|---------|
+| `NBA_ENTRIES_PATH` | Path to DKEntries.csv template from DraftKings |
+| `NBA_PROJS_DIR` | Directory containing NBA-Projs-*.csv projection files |
+| `NBA_LINEUP_DIR` | Base directory for intermediate lineup pools and ranked lineups |
+| `NBA_OUTPUT_DIR` | Directory for final upload-ready CSV exports |
+
+Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and set paths. Without real CSV input files, the pipeline will fail at data loading ‚Äî this is expected.
+
+## Build and Run
+
+```bash
+# Install
+pip install -e .
+
+# Run full pipeline (CLI)
+python scripts/run_optimizer.py -n 2500 -r 0.25
+
+# Run with GUI (requires wxPython display)
+python scripts/run_optimizer_gui.py
+
+# Run late swap
+python scripts/run_optimizer.py --late_swap
+
+# Run individual modules standalone
+python -m nba_optimizer.engine
+python -m nba_optimizer.ranker
+python -m nba_optimizer.exposure_report
+```
+
+**There are no linters, formatters, build steps, or automated tests configured.** Do not add them unless explicitly asked.
+
+## Coding Conventions
+
+### Naming
+
+- Files and functions: `snake_case`
+- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
+- Classes: `PascalCase`
+- DataFrame variables: `df_` prefix (e.g., `df_players`, `df_ranked`)
+- Lookup dicts/maps: `_dict` or `_map` suffix (e.g., `salary_dict`, `proj_map`)
+- Config instances: `cfg` or `config`
+
+### Imports
+
+- **Inside `src/nba_optimizer/`**: Use relative imports (`from . import config`, `from .utils import get_latest_file`)
+- **In `scripts/`**: Use absolute package imports (`from nba_optimizer import engine, ranker`)
+- Import order: stdlib ‚Üí third-party ‚Üí local
+
+### Error handling and logging
+
+- Use `print()` for all output ‚Äî no logging framework
+- Wrap `run()` functions in `try/except` with `print(f"Error: {e}")` and `traceback.print_exc()`
+- Progress is printed at 20% intervals during engine generation
+
+### Configuration pattern
+
+- All module `run()` functions accept a `Config` instance (dependency injection)
+- Use `dataclasses.replace()` to override Config defaults with CLI arguments
+- Each module has its own `main()` with `argparse` for standalone execution
+
+## Critical Pitfalls
+
+1. **Stale file pickup**: Stages communicate via timestamped CSVs. If a stage fails, stale outputs from a previous run may be picked up by the next stage. Be careful with any "latest file" logic.
+
+2. **Dual data loading**: `engine.py` and `late_swapper.py` each have their own `load_data()` with subtly different CSV parsing. If you change projection or DKEntries parsing, **check both files for parity**.
+
+3. **Cross-module coupling**: `ranker.py` imports `engine.load_data()`. Avoid creating more cross-module dependencies unless intentionally refactoring shared data loading.
+
+4. **High-risk files**: `engine.py` and `late_swapper.py` are the largest, highest-churn, and untested files. Changes here require extra care and manual verification.
+
+5. **No automated tests**: There is no test suite. Verify changes manually with real CSV inputs and output inspection. Do not add generic tests just for coverage ‚Äî any future tests must be transparent, domain-relevant, and directly tied to real optimizer behavior.
+
+6. **GUI dependencies**: `Gooey` and `wxPython` require a display server. The GUI will not work in headless/CI environments. This is expected.
+
+7. **Windows-specific considerations**: `ProcessPoolExecutor` pickles the full DataFrame per worker on Windows (no copy-on-write). The project was originally designed for Windows paths.
+
